default3.1default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultA key factor driving the development of AMR is 
defaultthe lack of rapid diagnostic and 
defaultdisease 
defaultsurveillance technologies 
defaultto 
defaultdetect early-stage infections in community settings.
default1
default-6
default 
defaultThe
default result is that
default worldwide many infections remain undiagnosed or are diagnosed at a late stage. This leads to on-going transmission 
defaultby 
defaultpeople
default unaware of their infections
default and
default widespread inappropriate use of antibiotics which fuels drug-
defaultresistance. Late diagnosis
default also 
defaultlimits
default 
defaultour ability to 
defaultrespond to
default 
defaultemerging 
defaultAMR strains
default.
default&#xa0;
default3.2default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultEarly detection plays a crucial role in all treatment and prevention strategies. 
defaultH
defaultowever,
default current gold-standard diagnostic tests 
default(
defaulte.g. 
defaultRT-PCR and bacterial culture) are slow and 
defaultrequire samples to be sent to specialist laboratories
default. This leads to
default inherent delays between tests, results and clinical interventions. Public health interventio
defaultn may be further delayed by a 
defaulttime lag of 1-2 weeks
default,
default associated with retrospective surveillance of laboratory tests.
default&#xa0;
default3.3default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultThere are national and international drivers to widen access to 
defaultrapid 
defaulttests at the point-of-care (
defaultPoC
default) but current tests (
defaulte.g.
default 
defaultlateral flow
default tests
default) are typically not sensitive to early infections
default,
default leading to missed opportunities for interventions.
default6
default 
default&#xa0;
default3.4default&#xa0;&#xa0; 
defaultMoreover while 
defaultPoC
default tests may speed diagnosis, 
defaultthis data must be captured. I
defaultf capability to capture information for national and international surveillance is lost, so too will our ability to respond to future threats.
default Therefore future rapid 
defaultPoC
default tests must be sensitive to early infections and combined with data linkage.
